<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FE17DB59FDAED549" box="[416,517,1567,1586]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FE17DB59FDAED549" box="[416,517,1567,1586]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FDF6DB59FD7CD549" author="CANDEZE E." bookContentInfo="1 - 534 + VI pls." box="[577,727,1567,1586]" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" part="17" refId="ref3850" refString="CANDEZE E. 1863: Monographie des elaterides, tome quatrieme. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege 17: 1 - 534 + VI pls." title="Monographie des elaterides, tome quatrieme" type="book" year="1863">CΑΝĐḔƶΕ (1863);</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FF02DB7CFECDD536" authority="Schaum" authorityName="Schaum" authorityYear="1852" box="[181,358,1594,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FF02DB7CFEB1D536" box="[181,282,1594,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
Schaum
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FE38DB7CFDECD536" authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[399,583,1594,1613]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FE38DB7CFE5FD536" box="[399,500,1594,1613]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
].
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E5F2841EE1B4178FF20DB12FE96D5F9" blockId="1.[151,760,1327,1666]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="2EF00F6FEE1B4178FF20DB12FE96D5F9" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<treatmentCitation id="8F410E50EE1B4178FF20DB12FEE5D51C" author="PIC M." box="[151,334,1620,1639]" page="29" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FF20DB12FEE5D51C" authority="Pic, 1922: 29" authorityName="Pic" authorityPageNumber="29" authorityYear="1922" box="[151,334,1620,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Binhon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FF20DB12FF7ED51C" box="[151,213,1620,1639]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Binhon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FF6DDB12FEE5D51C" author="Pic" box="[218,334,1620,1639]" firstAuthor="Pic" journalOrPublisher="Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques" page="29" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 32" part="36" refId="ref4559" refString="PIC M. 1922: Nouveautes diverses. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques 36: 1 - 32." title="Nouveautes diverses" type="journal article" year="1922">Pic, 1922: 29</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. 
<typeStatus id="D15B96E3EE1B4178FEE2DB12FED4D51C" box="[341,383,1620,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<treatmentCitation id="8F410E50EE1B4178FE7ADB12FD32D51C" author="PIC M." box="[461,665,1620,1639]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FE7ADB12FD32D51C" authority="Pic, 1922" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1922" box="[461,665,1620,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Binhon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrum">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FE7ADB12FDE8D51C" box="[461,579,1620,1639]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Binhon atrum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FDFEDB12FD32D51C" author="Pic" box="[585,665,1620,1639]" firstAuthor="Pic" journalOrPublisher="Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 32" part="36" refId="ref4559" refString="PIC M. 1922: Nouveautes diverses. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques 36: 1 - 32." title="Nouveautes diverses" type="journal article" year="1922">Pic, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
(by monotypy); 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FF59DB29FE96D5F9" bold="true" box="[238,317,1647,1666]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">syn. nov.</emphasis>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="46FA7BCAEE1B4178FF20DBDDFB30DB6E" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0E5F2841EE1B4178FF20DBDDFA81D1EE" blockId="1.[151,760,1691,2066]" lastBlockId="1.[828,1438,190,2069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FF20DBDDFE54D5C9" bold="true" box="[151,511,1691,1714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Comments on the classification.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FDCFDBDDFD53D5C9" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[632,760,1691,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FDCFDBDDFD53D5C9" box="[632,760,1691,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by SർΗΑUΜ (1852) in his ‘ 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FDEFDBFDFED5D589" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Catalogus Coleopterorum Europae</emphasis>
’ for 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FE07DB9DFF7BD469" authority="Germar, 1824" authorityName="Germar" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Rhipiceridae" genus="Callirhipis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulosus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FE07DB9DFD32D589" box="[432,665,1755,1778]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Callirhipis angulosus</emphasis>
Germar, 1824
</taxonomicName>
, an enigmatic elaterid species from the Eastern Mediterranean (
<collectingCountry id="76F768D1EE1B4178FEABDA5DFEC7D449" box="[284,364,1819,1842]" name="Greece" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="76F768D1EE1B4178FEC2DA5DFE68D449" box="[373,451,1819,1842]" name="Turkey" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="76F768D1EE1B4178FE7BDA5DFDAED449" box="[460,517,1819,1842]" name="Syria" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Syria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="76F768D1EE1B4178FD82DA5DFDDAD449" box="[565,625,1819,1842]" name="Israel" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Israel</collectingCountry>
– see PĿΑŦıΑ &amp; NḖΜΕŦΗ 2011). Although Schaum’s act fully conforms with the conditions of 
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FE33DA1DFDA7D409" author="ICZN" bookContentInfo="xxix + 306 pp." box="[388,524,1883,1906]" firstAuthor="ICZN" journalOrPublisher="International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" refId="ref4218" refString="ICZN 1999: International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." title="International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth Edition" type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 12.2.5), many subsequent authors considered the genus a 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FDD6DA3DFD5CD4E9" box="[609,759,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">nomen nudum</emphasis>
and thus formally unavailable. Most importantly of the authors who thought Schaum’s name invalid, LΕCOΝŦΕ (1853) validated a new version of the name 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FDC7DA9DFD5AD489" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[624,753,2011,2034]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FDC7DA9DFD5AD489" box="[624,753,2011,2034]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, following an identification by Schaum of a newly described Californian species, 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBFFDDF8FCDED38E" authority="LeConte, 1853" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schaumii">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FBFFDDF8FA9AD3AE" box="[1096,1329,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus schaumii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FA8FDDF8FCDED38E" author="LeConte" firstAuthor="LeConte" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Philosophical Society, New Series" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="405 - 508" part="10" refId="ref4528" refString="LECONTE J. L. 1853: Revision of the Elateridae of the United States. Transactions of the American Philosophical Society, New Series 10: 405 - 508." title="Revision of the Elateridae of the United States" type="journal article" year="1853">LeConte, 1853</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which led to a different, broader concept of the genus for many years. LΑർORĐΑıRΕ (1857) and CΑΝĐḔƶΕ (1863) correctly attributed 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB24DC58FABFD24E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[1171,1300,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB24DC58FABFD24E" box="[1171,1300,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Schaum, but accepted LeConte’s broad definition to include both the Palaearctic and Nearctic species. Subsequently, apparently considering the Nearctic species as the ‘true’ 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC8BDCD8FC17D2CE" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[828,956,414,437]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC8BDCD8FC17D2CE" box="[828,956,414,437]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, HΕΥĐΕΝ (1883) proposed a new genus name 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC8BDCF8FC14D2AE" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1883" box="[828,959,446,469]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Ceroplastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC8BDCF8FC14D2AE" box="[828,959,446,469]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Ceroplastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Palaearctic taxon; unfortunately, as he did it again only in a catalogue and without description, several authors considered the name as unavailable. These authors (e.g. HΥඌĿOΡ 1921) incorrectly attributed the name 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC14DF78FB8DD12E" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1883" box="[931,1062,574,597]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Ceroplastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC14DF78FB8DD12E" box="[931,1062,574,597]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Ceroplastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to SΕıĐĿıŦƶ (1888a,b), who gave a redescription of the taxon in the generic part of both his ‘ 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FCF2DF38FC49D1EE" box="[837,994,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fauna Baltica</emphasis>
’ and ‘ 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB90DF38FAB1D1EE" box="[1063,1306,638,661]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fauna Transsylvanica</emphasis>
’.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E5F2841EE1B4178FCEDDFD8FB6ED68E" blockId="1.[828,1438,190,2069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBB7DFD8FB5CD1CE" baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[1024,1271,670,693]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulosus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FBB7DFD8FB5CD1CE" box="[1024,1271,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus angulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by RΕıŦŦΕR (1896) as a new genus and species: 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FAF4DFF8FB04D18E" authority="Reitter, 1896" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Pseudophyllocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atricolor">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FAF4DFF8FBB6D18E" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Pseudophyllocerus atricolor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FB95DF98FB04D18E" author="Reitter" box="[1058,1199,734,757]" firstAuthor="Reitter" journalOrPublisher="Wiener Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="233 - 240" part="15" refId="ref4690" refString="REITTER E. 1896: Abbildungen mit Beschreibungen zehn neuer Coleopteren aus der palearctischen Fauna. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung 15: 233 - 240 + pl. III." title="Abbildungen mit Beschreibungen zehn neuer Coleopteren aus der palearctischen Fauna" type="journal article" year="1896">Reitter, 1896</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; but its synonymy was soon recognized by SർΗඐΑRƶ (1897). SർΗඐΑRƶ (1902) was the first author to explicitly state that the Palaearctic and Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC70DE78FBEED02E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[967,1093,830,853]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC70DE78FBEED02E" box="[967,1093,830,853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species were not congeneric. He attributed the Palaearctic taxon name to CΑΝĐḔƶΕ (1863) and thus incorrectly considered it junior to LeConte’s name, so he proposed another replacement name, 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FAE6DED8FB89D0AE" authority="Schwarz, 1902" authorityName="Schwarz" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Cladocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FAE6DED8FCDCD0AE" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Cladocerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FCCADEF8FB89D0AE" author="Schwarz" box="[893,1058,958,981]" firstAuthor="Schwarz" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="199 - 201" part="1901" refId="ref4949" refString="SCHWARZ O. 1902: Ueber die Elateriden-Gattungen Plastocerus Le Conte und Octinodes Cand. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1901 (2): 199 - 201." title="Ueber die Elateriden-Gattungen Plastocerus Le Conte und Octinodes Cand" type="journal article" year="1902">Schwarz, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Schwarz’s name was immediately synonymised by HΕΥĐΕΝ (1902), who pointed out that his name 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FCC8DEB8FBA9D76E" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1883" box="[895,1026,1022,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Ceroplastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FCC8DEB8FBA9D76E" box="[895,1026,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Ceroplastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was senior – although he mentioned the later ‘ 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC1AD958FB8AD72E" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Catalogus coleopterorum Europae, Caucasi et Armeniae rossicae</emphasis>
’ (HΕΥĐΕΝ et al. 1891), and not the original ‘ 
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC16D918FA3ED70E" box="[929,1429,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Catalogus coleopterorum Europae et Caucasi</emphasis>
’ (HΕΥĐΕΝ et al. 1883). In addition, HΕΥĐΕΝ (1902) noted that 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FCD9D9D8FBFAD7CE" authority="Schwarz" authorityName="Schwarz" authorityYear="1902" box="[878,1105,1182,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Cladocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FCD9D9D8FC40D7CE" box="[878,1003,1182,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Cladocerus</emphasis>
Schwarz
</taxonomicName>
is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FADBD9D8FBE6D7AE" authority="Kirsch, 1865: 68" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityPageNumber="68" authorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Cladocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FADBD9D8FC39D7AE" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Cladocerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FC2FD9F8FBE6D7AE" author="Kirsch" box="[920,1101,1214,1237]" firstAuthor="Kirsch" journalOrPublisher="Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift" page="68" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="40 - 104" part="9" refId="ref4363" refString="KIRSCH T. 1865: Beitrage zur Kaferfauna von Bogota. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 9: 40 - 104 + pl. III." title="Beitrage zur Kaferfauna von Bogota" type="journal article" year="1865">Kirsch, 1865: 68</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBECD9F8FB72D7AE" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1115,1241,1214,1237]" class="Magnoliopsida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB55D9F8FA91D7AE" box="[1250,1338,1214,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lycidae</taxonomicName>
) [in fact, KıRඌർΗ (1865) described 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBE1D998FB78D78E" box="[1110,1235,1246,1269]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Cladoceras" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FBE1D998FB78D78E" box="[1110,1235,1246,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Cladoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB54D998FACBD78E" authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1865" box="[1251,1376,1246,1269]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Cladocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB54D998FACBD78E" box="[1251,1376,1246,1269]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Cladocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is its unjustified emendation by GΕΜΜıΝǤΕR &amp; HΑROĿĐ (1869: 1633)]. For the next 70 years, 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBC1D858FB5FD64E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[1142,1268,1310,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FBC1D858FB5FD64E" box="[1142,1268,1310,1333]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was considered to be an American genus and 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBCCD878FB55D62E" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1883" box="[1147,1278,1342,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Ceroplastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FBCCD878FB55D62E" box="[1147,1278,1342,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Ceroplastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the genus occurring in the Old World, until CROඐඌOΝ (1972) corrected the usage: recognizing 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB37D838FACAD6EE" authority="Schaum" authorityName="Schaum" authorityYear="1852" box="[1152,1377,1406,1429]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB37D838FAAAD6EE" box="[1152,1281,1406,1429]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
Schaum
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC8BD8D8FC15D6CE" authorityName="Heyden" authorityYear="1883" box="[828,958,1438,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Ceroplastus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC8BD8D8FC15D6CE" box="[828,958,1438,1461]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Ceroplastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its junior synonym, for the Mediterranean species, and replaced 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB95D8F8FAA8D6AE" authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[1058,1283,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB95D8F8FB0AD6AE" box="[1058,1185,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
with its junior synonym 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC11D898FB6AD68E" authority="Candeze, 1863" authorityName="Candeze" authorityYear="1863" box="[934,1217,1502,1525]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Octinodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC11D898FBBFD68E" box="[934,1044,1502,1525]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Octinodes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FBABD898FB6AD68E" author="Candeze" bookContentInfo="1 - 534 + VI pls." box="[1052,1217,1502,1525]" firstAuthor="Candeze" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="1 - 534" part="17" refId="ref3850" refString="CANDEZE E. 1863: Monographie des elaterides, tome quatrieme. Memoires de la Societe Royale des Sciences de Liege 17: 1 - 534 + VI pls." title="Monographie des elaterides, tome quatrieme" type="book" year="1863">Candèze, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E5F2841EE1B4178FCEDD8B8FB30DB6E" blockId="1.[828,1438,190,2069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
SർΗΑUΜ (1852) originally placed 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB45D8B8FAD1D56E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[1266,1402,1534,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FB45D8B8FAD1D56E" box="[1266,1402,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC01DB58FBE9D54E" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[950,1090,1566,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Cebrionidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cebrionidae</taxonomicName>
. However, LΑർORĐΑıRΕ (1857) included 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC12DB78FB83D52E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[933,1064,1598,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC12DB78FB83D52E" box="[933,1064,1598,1621]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the family 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB67DB78FAEFD52E" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1232,1348,1598,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Elateridae</taxonomicName>
, where, with the single sojourn to the 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FB26DB18FAB4D50E" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1834" box="[1169,1311,1630,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Rhipiceridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Rhipiceridae</taxonomicName>
in HΥඌĿOΡ (1921), it remained until CROඐඌOΝ (1972) placed it in its own family, 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC50DBD8FB2BD5CE" authorityName="Crowson" authorityYear="1972" box="[999,1152,1694,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Plastoceridae</taxonomicName>
. Quite recently, BOർΑκ et al. (2018) and KUඌΥ et al. (2018) revised the taxonomic placement of 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FC65DB98FBFED58E" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1853" box="[978,1109,1758,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" genus="Plastocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3C94F453EE1B4178FC65DB98FBFED58E" box="[978,1109,1758,1781]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Plastocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using molecular analysis and downgraded its status to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FAB7DBB8FA3CD46E" box="[1280,1431,1790,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Plastocerinae">Plastocerinae</taxonomicName>
, back in the family 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FBB6DA58FBD8D44E" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1025,1139,1822,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Elateridae</taxonomicName>
. However, the family group name 
<taxonomicName id="C9E053C2EE1B4178FCCBDA78FB13D42E" authority="Crowson, 1972" authorityName="Crowson" authorityYear="1972" box="[892,1208,1854,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Plastoceridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Plastoceridae 
<bibRefCitation id="6A7155B0EE1B4178FBA4DA78FB13D42E" author="Crowson" box="[1043,1208,1854,1877]" firstAuthor="Crowson" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Universidad de Madrid" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" pagination="35 - 77" part="21" refId="ref3880" refString="CROWSON R. A. 1972: A review of the classification of Cantharoidea (Coleoptera), with the definition of two new families, Cneoglossidae and Omethidae. Revista de la Universidad de Madrid 21 (82): 35 - 77." title="A review of the classification of Cantharoidea (Coleoptera), with the definition of two new families, Cneoglossidae and Omethidae" type="journal article" year="1972">Crowson, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior homonym of Plastocerini LeConte, 1861. Although BOUർΗΑRĐ et al. (2011) called for a petition to the International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature to suppress the LeConte name, no such petition is listed on the ICZN website, so the name is still officially invalid (https:// www.iczn.org/cases/all-cases/).
</paragraph>
